                <h1>"The Yellow Wallpaper: A Study Guide"</h1>
                <p>"The Yellow Wallpaper" by Charlotte Perkins Gilman explores themes of mental health, gender roles, and the dangers of isolation. The story follows a woman confined to a room by her physician husband, where she becomes obsessed with the wallpaper. Her descent into madness symbolizes the struggles faced by women in a patriarchal society.</p>
